# How to use the Node.js REPL

This article should define and describe the Node.js Read-Eval-Print Loop (REPL), and enumerate some of its uses.

- The Node REPL is a command interpreter - you can feed it JS
- Good for testing and experimentation
- Discuss REPL idiosyncrasies: `var x = 5` sets a value, `x = 5` sets and returns it; etc.
- Give a use case or two